cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "claude-db: multi-paradigm database design, audit, and migration toolkit for Claude Code"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Enrique
    family-names: Rocha
    email: enriqueers98@gmail.com
    website: "https://tododeia.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Hainrixz/claude-db"
url: "https://github.com/Hainrixz/claude-db"
abstract: >-
  claude-db is an MIT-licensed Claude Code plugin that turns Claude into a senior multi-paradigm
  database expert. It designs new schemas, audits existing databases on two independent axes
  (Design & Integrity and Performance & Scale), and plans safe, reversible migrations across
  relational, document, key-value, wide-column, vector, time-series, and graph engines. Findings are
  falsifiable (observed evidence plus a runnable verification command), magnitudes are banded, and the
  tool never fabricates statistics or prices.
keywords:
  - database
  - schema-design
  - data-modeling
  - indexing
  - migrations
  - nosql
  - vector-database
  - claude-code
